3.01	Internal_exile	Internal Exile	Internal Exile ("A Collection of a Boy's Own Stories") was Fish's second solo album after leaving Marillion in 1988. The album, released 28 October 1991, was inspired by the singer's past, his own personal problems and his troubled experiences with his previous record label EMI.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/06/FishInternalExileOriginal.jpg/220px-FishInternalExileOriginal.jpg
